Date: 29 Aug 2000 13:58:48 -0400
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: Reuters Online, 29 Aug 2000 2:42 AM EST [edited
[1
Dengue Fever Kills 47 in Bangladesh
-----------------------------------
DHAKA: Mosquito-borne dengue fever has killed at least 47 people in
Bangladesh over the past 6 weeks, health officials said Tuesday. Dr. Kanak
Ranjan Talukder, a director of the government's Health Directorate, told
Reuters on Tuesday 29 Aug 2000, that "We have so far received
[notification of 47 deaths and 2 657 people affected by the disease all
over the country since July". He said that 31 of the deaths were in the
capital, Dhaka.
Dengue fever, for which there is no vaccine, causes excruciating muscle and
joint pains, high fever and severe headaches. In its severest form [DHF,
it causes internal bleeding and death.
