[2
Date: 1 Sep 2000 15:39:07 GMT
From: M. Cosgriff <mcosgriff@hotmail.com>
Source: Daily Star, 1 Spe 2000 [edited

Dengue: 22 more hospitalized in Dhaka
-------------------------------------
DHAKA: Twenty-two more people with dengue fever were admitted to different
hospitals and clinics in the city yesterday. The Central Control Room at
the Health Directorate said, Dhaka Medical College Hospital eported
admitting 3 patients, Mitford Hospital one, Dhaka Shishu Hospital and
BIRDEM 2 each, Bangladesh Medical College and Monwara Hospitals 4 each, Ibn
Sina Clinic 2, Central Hospital in Green Road one, Samarita Hospital 2 and
Al-Raji Hospital one.
The Control Room also reported admission of 9 dengue patients to the
Chittagong Medical College Hospital and 3 to Khulna Medical College Hospital.
Forty-eight people have so far died of dengue hemorrhagic fever and Dengue
Shock Syndrome (DHF, DSS) across the country.
